article.description: Adaora Elonu scored 14 points and Texas A&M (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) rolled to a 79-51 victory over Texas Tech Saturday night.
article.headline: Adaora Elonu, Texas A&M roll past Texas Tech
article.linkText: Texas A&M bounces back, rolls past Texas Tech
article.story:
COLLEGE STATION, Texas -- Adaora Elonu scored 14 points and Texas A&M (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) rolled to a 79-51 victory over Texas Tech Saturday night.

Tyra White and Alexia Standish scored 13 points apiece, Karla Gilbert scored 11 in a reserve role and Kelsey Bone had 10 points, 11 rebounds, five assists and three blocked shots for the Aggies (20-7, 11-5 Big 12). Texas A&M shot 59 percent, led by double figures beginning midway through the first half and held a 36-18 halftime edge in getting ready for its next game, Monday night at home against No. 1 Baylor.

Casey Morris led the Lady Raiders (17-11, 5-11) with 15 points. Texas Tech has lost four in a row.

The Aggies bounced back from a 64-55 loss at Oklahoma on Thursday. Texas A&M has two Big 12 games remaining, Baylor and Texas. Baylor (29-0) won the previous meeting 71-48 two weeks ago in Waco, Texas.
